{"article_id":"XBDnYN2QW0LOm8wl","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell has made it clear to President Donald Trump","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"that he has a choice :","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Move ahead with his emergency declaration at the border","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"and risk of a rebuke from his own party","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"or shift gears .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"McConnell acknowledged Monday","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"the Senate is likely to pass a resolution","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"to block Trump ' s emergency declaration at the southern border .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"Since the measure has already cleared the House ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Senate passage would send it to Trump 's desk .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"\" I think","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"what is clear in the Senate is there will be enough votes","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"to pass the resolution of disapproval ,","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"which will then be vetoed by the president , \"","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"McConnell told reporters in Kentucky .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"\" And then , in all likelihood , the veto will be upheld in the House . \"","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Mitch McConnell :","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"It 's clear","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Senate will vote against President Trump 's national emergency","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"Rand Paul :","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"Kentucky senator says","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"he 'll vote to block Trump 's emergency declaration","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Start the day smarter :","depth":4},{"id":25,"text":"Get 's Daily Briefing in your inbox","depth":4},{"id":26,"text":"Trump has threatened to veto the resolution","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"if it passes both chambers of Congress","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"and lawmakers have said","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"the emergency order 's opponents do not appear to have enough votes in either the House or the Senate","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"to override a presidential veto .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"Even so , the struggle over the emergency order would mark a turning point in Trump 's presidency .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Not only would it be the first time","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Trump has issued a veto ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"it would put him at odds with members of his own party over how to deliver one of the key promises of his 2016 presidential campaign .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Republicans say","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"while they support Trump ' s objective","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"- building a wall along the U.S.-Mexico border -","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"several have serious reservations","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"about declaring a national emergency","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"to free up billions of dollars for the structure .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Some lawmakers also have raised concerns","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"that Trump will be diverting from key military programs","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"to fund the barrier .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Trump declared a national emergency along the border on Feb. 15","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"to free up money for a border wall .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"The decision came","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"after Congress refused to give him the $ 5.7 billion","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"he had demanded for the barrier .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Trump said","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"he wants the wall","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"to stop drugs and gangs from coming into the U.S. ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"even though an analysis of data indicates","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"the vast majority of narcotics enters through country ports of entry , not the wide swaths of border in between","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"where additional barriers could be erected ,","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"experts say .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul , R-Ky. , was the latest GOP senator","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"to voice objections to an emergency declaration .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Paul said during a speech in Kentucky on Saturday","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"that approving the emergency declaration would be tantamount to giving \" extra-Constitutional powers to the president \"","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"- something","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"he said","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"he ' s unwilling to do .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"' I did n't need to do this . ' :","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Critics say","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Trump quote undercuts national emergency for border wall","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"\" I can ' t vote to give the president the power","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"to spend money","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"that hasn ' t been appropriated by Congress , \"","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"Paul said ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"as reported by the Bowling Green Daily News .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"\" We may want more money for border security ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"but Congress didn ' t authorize it .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"If we take away those checks and balances ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"it ' s a dangerous thing . \"","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Some House Republicans made the same argument last week ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"when 13 of them joined all Democrats","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"in voting","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"to block Trump 's declaration ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"sending the measure to the Senate .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"McConnell has said","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"the Senate will take up the measure by March 15 .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"Meanwhile , some GOP senators are looking to give Trump a way out .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"Sen. Lamar Alexander , R-Tenn. ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"who has called an emergency declaration `` inconsistent with the U.S. Constitution , ''","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"offered an alternative last week .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"Instead of declaring a national emergency ,","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"Alexander suggested","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Trump could secure money for his border wall","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"by tapping into funds","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"that Congress already approved for various programs .","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"Not only would that give Trump access to the money","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"he wants ,","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"it could potentially avoid months and years of litigation ,","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"Alexander said .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"National emergency :","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"Donald Trump declares national emergency","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"to free up billions of dollars for border wall","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"As the Senate vote approaches ,","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"several GOP senators said","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"they 're still deciding how they will vote .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"Others support Trump ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"he ' s doing what he needs to do","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"to protect the nation ' s borders .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"\" The president ' s not exercising any power","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"that Congress didn ' t give him , ''","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"said Sen. John Kennedy , R-La .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"\" Had Congress done its job","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"instead of playing politics ,","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"he wouldn ' t have to do it . \"","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"Democrats , meanwhile , have complained","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"Trump is trying to do an \" end run around the Constitution . ''","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"\" This is a president","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"who is grasping for power ,","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"and he has to be reined in , ''","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"said New Mexico Sen. Tom Udall ,","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"who serves on the Senate Appropriations Committee .","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"Paul 's weekend announcement","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"that he opposes the emergency declaration","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"makes him the fourth Senate Republican","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"who has said","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"they will vote to stop it .","depth":15},{"id":124,"text":"His decision gives opponents the 51 votes","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"they need","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"to block Trump 's declaration .","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"The other three Republicans","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"who have said","depth":15},{"id":129,"text":"they will vote","depth":16},{"id":130,"text":"to stop the declaration","depth":16},{"id":131,"text":"are Thom Tillis of North Carolina , Susan Collins of Maine and Lisa Murkowski of Alaska .","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"`` As a U.S. senator , I can not justify providing the executive with more ways","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"to bypass Congress , ''","depth":16},{"id":134,"text":"Tillis wrote in an op-ed in The Washington Post ,","depth":16},{"id":135,"text":"laying out his concerns .","depth":16},{"id":136,"text":"`` As a conservative , I can not endorse a precedent","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"that","depth":17},{"id":138,"text":"I know","depth":17},{"id":139,"text":"future left-wing presidents will exploit","depth":17},{"id":140,"text":"to advance radical policies","depth":18},{"id":141,"text":"that will erode economic and individual freedoms . ''","depth":18},{"id":142,"text":"Tillis was elected in 2014","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"and is up for re-election in 2020 .","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"The nonpartisan Cook Political Report has rated the seat \" likely Republican . \"","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"Collins ,","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"who is also up for re-election next year ,","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"she ' s concerned about Trump using the declaration","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"to repurpose billions of dollars","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"that Congress has already appropriated .","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"It \" strikes me as undermining the appropriations process , the will of Congress","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"and of being of dubious constitutionality , ''","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"she said .","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"Collins ,","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"who is serving her fourth term ,","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"is a moderate Republican","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"who sometimes breaks with her party on key issues ,","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"including health care .","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"She criticized a federal judge 's ruling last December","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"to overturn the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"it was \" too sweeping . \"","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"She was also among the three Republicans ,","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"including the late Arizona Sen. John McCain and Lisa Murkowski of Alaska ,","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"who voted last summer against the Republican 's \" skinny repeal bill , \" killing the GOP health care measure .","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"All eyes were also on Collins last fall","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"when the Senate voted on the controversial confirmation of U.S. Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh ,","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"who had come under fire for accusations of sexual assault","depth":15},{"id":169,"text":"committed decades ago .","depth":15},{"id":170,"text":"Collins ,","depth":16},{"id":171,"text":"who had been on the fence for months ,","depth":16},{"id":172,"text":"voted for Kavanaugh ,","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"saying","depth":15},{"id":174,"text":"that voting against him","depth":17},{"id":175,"text":"without witnesses or proof","depth":17},{"id":176,"text":"could start a `` dangerous '' precedent .","depth":16},{"id":177,"text":"And as recently as last week Collins was the lone Republican","depth":16},{"id":178,"text":"to oppose the nomination of Andrew Wheeler ,","depth":17},{"id":179,"text":"who was narrowly confirmed as Trump ' s pick","depth":18},{"id":180,"text":"to head the Environmental Protection Agency .","depth":18},{"id":181,"text":"Collins said","depth":16},{"id":182,"text":"she opposed the nomination","depth":17},{"id":183,"text":"because , as acting administrator , Wheeler supported policies","depth":18},{"id":184,"text":"that \" are not in the best interest of our environment and public health ,","depth":19},{"id":185,"text":"particularly given the threat of climate change to our nation . ''","depth":19},{"id":186,"text":"Murkowski said","depth":15},{"id":187,"text":"she will support the resolution","depth":16},{"id":188,"text":"to block Trump 's emergency declaration .","depth":16},{"id":189,"text":"Murkowski ,","depth":17},{"id":190,"text":"who has been in the Senate since 2002 ,","depth":17},{"id":191,"text":"is up for re-election in 2022 .","depth":16},{"id":192,"text":"She shocked the political world in 2010","depth":16},{"id":193,"text":"when she waged a successful write-in campaign","depth":17},{"id":194,"text":"after losing her party ' s primary .","depth":17},{"id":195,"text":"Murkowski , the daughter of former Alaska governor and senator Frank Murkowski , has at other times refused to vote in lockstep with the national party","depth":16},{"id":196,"text":"that","depth":18},{"id":197,"text":"some say","depth":18},{"id":198,"text":"abandoned her during her re-election bid .","depth":17},{"id":199,"text":"Murkowski was the only Republican","depth":19},{"id":200,"text":"to vote against Kavanaugh 's appointment .","depth":19},{"id":201,"text":"She voted \" present \" as a collegial gesture for her Republican colleague Sen. Steve Daines ,","depth":19},{"id":202,"text":"who supported Kavanaugh","depth":20},{"id":203,"text":"but was attending his daughter 's wedding .","depth":20},{"id":204,"text":"Murkowski has worked across the aisle on issues important to her state ,","depth":18},{"id":205,"text":"including with former Democrat Sen. Mary Landrieu of Louisiana on energy policies .","depth":18},{"id":206,"text":"Murkowski , along with Collins , also voted against the confirmation of Betsy DeVos , Trump ' s choice","depth":17},{"id":207,"text":"to head the Department of Education .","depth":17},{"id":208,"text":"Arizona ' s Sen. Martha McSally , a newcomer to the chamber , also has voiced concerns about the emergency declaration .","depth":15},{"id":209,"text":"McSally ,","depth":18},{"id":210,"text":"appointed last December","depth":19},{"id":211,"text":"to fill McCain 's seat ,","depth":19},{"id":212,"text":"said recently","depth":17},{"id":213,"text":"she was `` seeking assurances","depth":18},{"id":214,"text":"that the money will not come from Arizona military construction projects ''","depth":18},{"id":215,"text":"for her vote","depth":18},{"id":216,"text":"supporting the president .","depth":18},{"id":217,"text":"McSally is expected to face a competitive race in the 2020 special election .","depth":14},{"id":218,"text":"The Cook Political Report rates the seat `` leans Republican . ''","depth":13},{"id":219,"text":"Earlier this month , Mark Kelly , a retired U.S. Navy pilot and the husband of former Rep. Gabby Giffords , announced his plans","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"to run for the seat .","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"Despite concerns","depth":14},{"id":222,"text":"raised by some GOP lawmakers ,","depth":14},{"id":223,"text":"only 13 broke ranks with the party","depth":15},{"id":224,"text":"and voted in favor of the Democratic backed resolution","depth":16},{"id":225,"text":"when it passed the House last week .","depth":16},{"id":226,"text":"Several of them ,","depth":16},{"id":227,"text":"including Reps. Will Hurd of Texas , Brian Fitzpatrick of Pennsylvania and Fred Upton of Michigan ,","depth":16},{"id":228,"text":"are expected to run in competitive races in 2020 .","depth":15},{"id":229,"text":"Most Republicans voted along party lines and against the resolution ,","depth":13},{"id":230,"text":"citing the need for more border security .","depth":13}],"relations":[{"parent":461,"left":0,"right":460,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":460,"left":255,"right":459,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":255,"left":253,"right":254,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":247,"right":252,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":236,"right":246,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":236,"left":1,"right":235,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":235,"left":2,"right":234,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":234,"left":233,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":232,"right":5,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":246,"left":240,"right":245,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":240,"left":238,"right":239,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":7,"right":237,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":237,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":245,"left":244,"right":17,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":244,"left":12,"right":243,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":243,"left":242,"right":16,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":13,"right":241,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"el